Financial Planners & Investment Advisers Industry Report















J. J. B. HILLIARD, W. L. LYONS, LLC Revenue and Financial Data

   Bluegrass and greenbacks? For J.J.B. Hilliard, W.L. Lyons (Hilliard Lyons for short) that may be a winning combination. Founded in Kentucky in 1854, the subsidiary of Houchens Industries provides customized wealth management services to retail investors and small business owners. It offers managed accounts; retirement and college savings plans; access to stocks, bonds, mutual funds, and insurance; and proprietary investment research, advice, and education. The company also provides investment banking services to closely held emerging and middle-market firms. Hilliard Lyons, with $499.6 million in total assets in fiscal 2013, boasts more than 70 offices in about a dozen Midwestern and Southern states.
  







